DSMR P1 Prometheus and Home Assistant/MQTT publisher

A Dutch Smart Meter Requirements (DSMR) publisher

This software lets you read out DSMR Object Identification System (OBIS) data
from the P1 port of the Dutch smart meter and publish it for the Prometheus
database and Home Assistant using the MQTT protocol. It can be invoked by
systemd at startup.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Create /etc/dsmr_publisher.conf

[serial]
device: /dev/ttyUSB0

[prometheus]
hostname: 127.0.0.1
port: 8888


[mqtt]
hostname: 192.168.1.206
port: 8888
username: mqtt_user
password: password
keepalive: 60

reconnect_initial: 1
reconnect_max: 60
reconnect_jitter: 20

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Create /etc/systemd/system/dsmr_publisher.service:

[Unit]
Description=DSMR Publisher
After=network.target

[Service]
ExecStart=/usr/local/bin/dsmr_publisher
Restart=always
User=p1
Group=dialout
WatchdogSec=10
NotifyAccess=all
NoNewPrivileges=yes
PrivateTmp=yes
ProtectSystem=strict
ProtectHome=yes

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Create the p1 user

sudo useradd -r p1
sudo usermod -a -G dialout p1
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable --now dsmr_publisher

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Prometheus scrape in /etc/prometheus/prometheus.yml:

scrape_configs:
  - job_name: 'dsmr_publisher'
    static_configs:
    - targets: ['localhost:8888']

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Final notes (important)
    Gas updates hourly -> use increase() in PromQL
    Power totals != sum of phases (DSMR behavior)
    Export per phase is essential for PV imbalance analysis
    CRC is included but can be enforced per-telegram if desired

